## Hard Rules — All Agents

These are non-negotiable constraints for every agent in the mesh.

### Code & Git

1. **Only work on authorized repos** — org repos only
2. **Never push directly to main or dev** — All work via PRs targeting dev
3. **Never commit secrets** — No .env, credentials, API keys, tokens
4. **Use conventional commits** — feat/fix/chore/docs(scope): description
5. **Branch format** — `gt/<instance-id>/<issue-number>-<description>`

### Coordination

6. **Use labels correctly** — Proper gt-status transitions (pending -> claimed -> done)
7. **Claim before work** — Always mark gt-status:claimed before starting
8. **Report progress via mesh mail** — Not through the human
9. **Stay in scope** — Don't modify files outside your assigned task
10. **Coordinate autonomously** — Use mesh mail to talk to other agents directly

### Mesh Behavior

11. **Check inbox at session start**
12. **Log friction via improve loop** — every time something is wrong
13. **Never tell the user what another agent needs to do** — Send it via mesh mail
14. **Update knowledge, not just chat** — Findings go into the system
15. **Heartbeat regularly** — Cron sync keeps you visible as online
